<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I haven't touched a forgotten realms book in years. Liked whatever the first Drizz't book was (Can't even remember the name now.  It's been that long) but found that the series largely degenerated into "look how cool my characters are!" after about the 2nd or 3rd.   Not many authors can really sustain good fiction on a common theme over more than three or four books, I find.  (I haven't read the Dark Tower, so I'm willing to cut Mr. King the benefit of the doubt in this regard, but it holds true for every other longer series I can think of.)
<br />

<br />
I haven't had a lot of success finding good new fiction lately - though I'm about halfway through Garth Nix's <span style="font-style: italic">Sabriel</span> and enjoying it thoroughly.  I also liked <span style="font-style: italic">The Dreaming Tree</span> by C.J. Cheryh, though the first half was rather better than the 2nd, it was still an interesting and compelling - as well as creative and new, to me at any rate - story and device.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
