<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Frank Herbert - fantastic series, and yes, it is for a thinking person, but damn finely written
<br />

<br />
Modesitt's Recluse series is awesome. Although I prefer the early series based around the Order guys.
<br />

<br />
Donaldson's Thomas Convenant series was good. I am also waiting for the next book to come out before I pick up the new series.
<br />

<br />
Robert Jordan's series is good although, he REALLY needs to taking a writing class in order to figure out WHEN TO STOP!!!!!
<br />

<br />
George Martin's series is also good although, a little choppy as he has too many chracters for my taste.
<br />

<br />
David Farland's Runelord series is also a good choice. Trilogy starts with "The Runelords"
<br />

<br />
I really enjoyed all of the Dark Sun books from TSR. They were well written and the game world is pretty interesting. 
<br />

<br />
Feist's early works were nice. The later works were.. well.. a bit lacking IMHO.
<br />

<br />
Joel Rosenberg's Guardians of the Flame series is also good.
<br />

<br />
Phylassein had a good point with Brian Lumley. I personally can't stand Rice's vampire series,  but Lumley takes an interesting twist on things, which I enjoyed.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
