<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Saediien wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Are there multiple bits of the Hedge Knight series?  I've just read the one graphic novella, which was pretty good.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
To the best of my knowledge, there are two.  I’m still waiting for more of these also…
<br />

<br />
The Hedge Knight was originally published in the Legends compilation.  This is the story that the “graphic novel” was written from.  Other than losing some description because it was shown, it’s the exact story.
<br />

<br />
There are about 10-12 authors that all wrote a short story based in their worlds.  While George R. R. Martin’s Hedge Knight was my favorite, they were all extremely well written and worth the time.  This compilation came out in hardback around 1997ish I believe.  I could be off as I usually am.  But, it was re-released in 3 parts, paperback style.
<br />

<br />
Then, Legends compilation #2 came out.  This was a couple years ago now I think.  Dunk and Egg have been together a while and have traveled quite a bit and end up in a very small keep working for a family that was once great, but have fallen far.  IMO, it’s at least as good as the original Hedge Knight.  Unfortunately, I can’t think of the title to this story.
<br />

<br />
In case anyone was wondering…. Yes I do wander Barnes & Noble (or equivalent as available) quite a lot.  It’s actually how I can across the Legends compilations and most of the other authors I read.  I usually wander for about 4+ hours and walk out with about 5 or 6 new books.  Once they’re done, I head back for another barrage of reading.  I’m currently finishing my last book before I’m off to find my next set.
<br />

<br />
Hmmm… I get paid Friday…..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
